				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {H}_2\hbox {O}$$\end{document} in O-CSEs, and CO and HCN in C-CSEs. Most of the heating and cooling terms used in radiative transfer codes are given in the form of analytical descriptions for which the validity in certain parameter ranges can be questioned. As a guideline, over a sizable radial range the kinetic temperature distribution can be approximated by a power law, r-ϵ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
