The dust temperature is locally determined by a balance between the absorption of the infalling radiation (at shorter wavelengths) and the subsequent reemission (at longer wavelengths), see Sect. 1.3. This is discussed further in Sect. 4.2. The result is a dust temperature distribution that is fairly shallow as a function of r, ϵ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
