Mono-chromatic flux density estimate In its simplest form, a “mono-chromatic” flux density is used as a dust-mass-loss-rate estimator, a method that rests on substantial simplifications. In the past, estimates based on, e.g., the IRAS 60μm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
