Flux excess and colour estimate A considerable improvement in accuracy is obtained using a flux excess (the flux density in excess of that of the star), or using two (well-selected) flux densities and form their ratio, i.e., a colour. The relations used for estimating dust-mass-loss rate from flux excess or colour are either calibrated against other methods, or they are derived from theory for the particular dust composition in question. An example of a flux-excess estimate is provided by the work of Srinivasan et al. (2009) that is based on the Spitzer 8μm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
