While uncertainties in empirical mass-loss rates and stellar parameter determinations are probably considerable (see Sect. 5.2.1), they cannot reasonably be made responsible for all of the discrepancies. Neither is it likely that the PEDDRO models are fundamentally wrong, given their good agreement with observed wind properties (M˙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
