To begin with, it should be noted that the trends derived from the models (e.g., expressed as exponents in a mass-loss formula) refer to the influence of individual stellar parameters, i.e., a situation where all other fundamental parameters are kept fixed, which will not be the case for observational samples. Taking the formula by Wachter et al. (2002) as an example, we can try to compensate for the offset in the theoretical trend with luminosity (M˙∝L∗2.47\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
