Another aspect of anisotropic CSEs are structures such as arcs and spiral patterns. The number of examples is steadily increasing, e.g., CW Leo (Cernicharo et al. 2015; Decin et al. 2015), RW LMi (Dinh-V-Trung 2009; Claussen et al. 2011; Kim et al. 2015), R Scl (Maercker et al. 2012), R Aqr and W Aql (Mayer et al. 2013), and π1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
